OSOGBO – Pandemonium ensued in the ancient city of Ile-Ife, Osun State, on Saturday as some angry youths took to the street to protest the death of a suspect simply identified as Olufemi Oriyomi who died in police custody. Oriyomi was arrested at Ile-Ife on Thursday in connection with alleged ritual killings along with two other suspects. The suspects simply identified as Olayade Kehinde (25), Olufemi Oriyomi( 21) and Raimi Sheriff ‘M’ (21) were alleged to have involved ritual killings and in possession h human parts. Unconfirmed report revealed that the suspect died in the course of interrogation by the police on the matter. It was gathered that the security operatives stormed Ile-Ife to arrest the suspects and later news went round that Oriyomi has passed on in the police customer. The development infuriated the youths in the town who alleged that the suspect was actually killed by the police in the course of their interrogation. Reacting to the incident, Osun State Police Command spokesperson, ASP Yemisi Opalola, confirmed the development. She explained that the suspects were arrested along Osogbo/OAU IFE Campus road while in a vehicle which police on surveillance suspected and stopped them. According to her, “The police on the April 7, 2022 at about 1100hrs along Osogbo/OAU Ife Campus Road, the Police detectives on ‘stop and search’ duty accosted three men on motorcycle.” She explained that the police suspected them and reportedly flagged them down but the suspects refused to stop and consequently sped off. POLL She stated that the police gave them a hot chase and arrested them at a point at Safejo area of Ile-Ife. In the process of conducting a search, a human part (the heart) carefully packaged in bag was discovered. In their confessional statement, they claimed it was a human heart.